      <div type="book">
        <linkGrp type="notes"/>
        <div n="935-740L" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-935-740L-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-935-740L-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-935-740L-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1">Sent by a Lady to a Gentleman.</l></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-935-740L-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-935-740L-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-935-740L-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1">The <lb/> Gentleman's Answer</l></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-935-740L-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-935-740L-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-935-740L-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-935-740L-line-1"> By Something form'd, I Nothing Am;&#13;</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-935-740L-line-2"> Yet every thing that you can Name.</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-935-740L-line-3"> In no place have I ever been;</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-935-740L-line-4"> Yet every where I may be seen.</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-935-740L-line-5"> In all things false, yet always true,</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-935-740L-line-6"> I'm still the same, but ever new,</l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-935-740L-line-7"> Lifeless, life's perfect Form I wear,</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-935-740L-line-8"> Can shew a Nose, eye, tongue and ear;</l><l n="9" xml:id="spp-935-740L-line-9"> Yet neither Smell, See, tast nor hear.</l><l n="10" xml:id="spp-935-740L-line-10"> All shapes and features I can boast,</l><l n="11" xml:id="spp-935-740L-line-11"> No flesh, no bones, no blood,────no Ghost!</l><l n="12" xml:id="spp-935-740L-line-12"> All colours without paint put on,</l><l n="13" xml:id="spp-935-740L-line-13"> And change like the Cameleon,</l><l n="14" xml:id="spp-935-740L-line-14"> Swiftly I come and enter there,</l><l n="15" xml:id="spp-935-740L-line-15"> Where not a chink lets in the Air;</l><l n="16" xml:id="spp-935-740L-line-16"> Like thought I'm in a moment gone,</l><l n="17" xml:id="spp-935-740L-line-17"> Nor can I ever be alone.</l><l n="18" xml:id="spp-935-740L-line-18"> All things on earth I imitate,</l><l n="19" xml:id="spp-935-740L-line-19"> Faster than Nature can create;</l><l n="20" xml:id="spp-935-740L-line-20"> Sometimes Imperial Robes I wear,</l><l n="21" xml:id="spp-935-740L-line-21"> Anon in Beggar's rags appear;</l><l n="22" xml:id="spp-935-740L-line-22"> A Giant now, and straight an Elf,</l><l n="23" xml:id="spp-935-740L-line-23"> I am every one, but ne'er my Self;</l><l n="24" xml:id="spp-935-740L-line-24"> Or Male, or Female,──────yet my sex</l><l n="25" xml:id="spp-935-740L-line-25"> No, Naturalist cou'd ever fix.</l><l n="26" xml:id="spp-935-740L-line-26"> Ne'er Sad I mourn, ne'er glad rejoice,</l><l n="27" xml:id="spp-935-740L-line-27"> I move my lips, but want a voice.</l><l n="28" xml:id="spp-935-740L-line-28"> I ne'er was born, nor ne'er can die;</l><l n="29" xml:id="spp-935-740L-line-29"> Then pre'thee tell me what am I?935-740L   </l></lg></div>
